I can’t believe I’m posting this. Man this one hurts so bad. I can’t stop crying. Mike Classic (@mikeclassic1) you were like a big brother to me. Always telling how proud you are, but man I looked up to you so much. One of the most talented people I’ve ever met. I’m so blessed that I got to spend some time with you in October. You were an outstanding father and just good guy period. No matter the circumstances you were always smiling. Not to many people in the world like you. The world lost a father, a brother, a Great Musician and good friend. You touched so many peoples lives. Love you forever Mike. 🕊️🫶🏾💔 your legacy will live on. I told you from Day 1 I got you. Forever my brother.

Going to keep your legacy and memory alive forever Mike.
So much we were supposed to do. 😢 #rip #ripmikeclassic

A great benefit of being an @ascap member. ASCAP members get a free month of therapy from @betterhelp 
This is such a great benefit. I wanted to share this message In light of some personal trauma I have encountered. Mental health in “our” community is very taboo to talk about and I’m here to change the narrative. So to all my brothers and sisters out there if you are in a mental health crisis and you need help please seek the help you need. Again if you are an Ascap member make sure you tap In to this great benifit🫶🏾. 

Disclaimer: I decided to make this post on my own, and share this knowledge. This is not a paid advertisement or endorsement. 

#mentalhealth #entertainment #ascap #creative #musician #producer #manager

A parent should never have to burry their child before themselves.  Hearing a mother cry like I heard today was so heartbreaking.  To all my brothers out there, hold your head up King. We see you, you are valued, you are appreciated, your are respected, you are loved. If you feel like the walls are closing in talk to someone. You can not self destruct. The impact suicide has on your tribe is a pain that never goes away. 
Love you forever bro @ad_thepen I will forever miss you. You were one of the most talented people I have had  the pleasure of knowing. You were good friend, and a good father. I wish we could’ve talked one more time. 
♾️ missed . 

#brotherhood #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #blackmen #message
